Adams Oshiomhole, a former governor of Edo State and ex-National Chairman of the All Progressives Congress, has faulted the Independent National Electoral Commission for deploying non-functional card readers for Saturday’s governorship election in the state. He spoke with journalists after casting his ballot at Polling Unit 01, Ward 10 in Uzairue North-East under Etsako West Local Government Area. Adams Oshiomhole He said, “Since 1999, this is the highest turnout that I have seen. Elderly women and men turned out impressively. “The turnout showed that people have shown that they are ready for democracy. My only disappointment so far is that the machine is not working. “The INEC officials have reported but they have not brought a new machine. See Also






